<part_of.title>Stay in Italy. For longer stay in Italy speeks the fact that Clovio was in Rome only 1553-1556 so Bruegel workinbg with him may well have stayed in Rome into 1554. From Rome he may have made the trip to Naples. Itinary can be partly reconstructed by works. Journey through France proved by 'Leon in France'. Stay in Italy: 2 prints 1553, Tivoli, Fondi drawing, Ripa Grande (?), Naples Harbour, Battle of Messina (Reggio), Palermo, Triumph of Death. Return: Tyrol, Martinswand, Walterspurg.</part_of.title>
